latestPosts.caption:
I was so scared to post this video, but then I thought, if I’m not going to promote or uplift myself, who will?

I have dry, acne-prone, sensitive skin, along with PCOD, so if you do too, you might find my content helpful since I’ve been experimenting with products for over 5 years now.
I’m not a dermatologist or an esthetician. Everything I’ve learned is from watching multiple dermatologists’ videos and researching online day and night.

Honesty and transparency are all I have, and that’s how I want to grow because that’s how I was raised. 

Now, I’m not saying I’ll never make a mistake, but accepting your mistakes and learning from them is how we grow as human beings.

So yes, if you love skincare as much as I do, don’t forget to check out my content. And if you like it, hit the follow button, and let’s do skincare together. 

Let’s learn together! 🫰🏻♥️

.

Personally, I absolutely love this sunscreen from @letshyphen 

I think it’s one of the few products from the brand that I genuinely liked. It has a really nice liquid texture, absorbs within seconds, and doesn’t leave that horrible white cast.

In this price range, I’ve tried sunscreens from other brands as well, but many of them leave a noticeable white cast, and the texture often isn’t great either.

So, considering the price, I feel like this product has performed really well.
